    "title": "Use offline dictionaries as fallback", 
    "comments": [
        {
            "date": "2012-02-10 15:58:21", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "When no internet connection can be established, lingo should use locally installed dictionaries as data source. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I use lingo a lot f.e. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "and sometimes I don't have an internet connection, which makes lingo useless. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "And I doubt I'm the only one who encounters that problem.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "sgo.ger", 
            "email": "sgo.ger"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-02-11 00:43:58", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Thanks for your report, Steve.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This gets discussed often, and here's what my position is:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Quality is the #1 issue.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The reason I went through the trouble of finding a free online dictionary API, communicating with the organization behind it, and implementing an API client for it is because I don't know of any offline dictionaries with solid quality.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Basically every other dictionary program for Linux uses WordNet, but I and others tend to agree that the results are far inferior from a professional, commercially-driven project that aggregates multiple data sources and spends a great deal of effort assuring quality. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "(In fact, Wordnik [the API Lingo currently uses] actually uses WordNet as one of its data sources).\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Effectively, I see it as a compromise between quality and convenience (or availability).\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "One potential solution is to, as you suggested, fall back to an offline dictionary when an Internet connection is not available. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The obvious problem with this is that Lingo would have different results of different (substantially lesser) quality when offline as opposed to offline.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It's a tricky situation, at best. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I'll leave this bug open for discussion, but that's where I stand as of now.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "aroman", 
            "email": "aroman"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-02-11 19:41:06", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I agree with aroman, we shouldn't have an offline dictionary.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "davidgomes", 
            "email": "davidgomes"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-02-13 01:03:57", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I understand the concern of having different results. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "That said, I personally do use a separate offline dictionary. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It is moot that it may be different if there's no network available. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Worse, I tend to prefer the offline dictionary because it works in both cases and I hate having to think about which one I need to use.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "kalikiana", 
            "email": "kalikiana"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-02-13 03:06:32", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Thanks for your fast and comprehensive answer, Aroman. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I understand the quality concerns, but I strongly agree with Christian here. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I tested lingo now for only a couple of weeks, but am about to install another dictionary just because I have to use it offline sometimes.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "A dictionary's purpose is to deliver you a definition of a word. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Of what use is it if it can't fulfill this purpose under some, common, circumstances? ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "All the nice, quality results it gets are worth nothing if you happen to be unable to connect to the internet.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I know the elementary philosophy is not to try to make it right for everyone, but I don't think that this should include the offline use of the operating system, should it?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "sgo.ger", 
            "email": "sgo.ger"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-04 14:03:22", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I think we could use Wiktionary for both non-English languages and as an offline-source, since it's possible to download it.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "voluntatefaber", 
            "email": "voluntatefaber"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-14 17:25:52", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I think Wiktionary has a serious quality issue, and a relatively low signal to noise ratio. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I would not be opposed to using it as a source, but only if an API could be written to spit back higher quality results for it. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Might be an excellent choice, in that case.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "aroman", 
            "email": "aroman"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-23 23:54:00", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The latest dump of Wiktionary is here: http://dumps.wikimedia.org/enwiktionary/20120320/\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The English Wiktionary (pretty sure it's the largest) is about 302MB. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I, for one, think that's pretty big.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I haven't done much research (pulled suggestions from here: http://www.linuxquestions.org/questions/linux-software-2/offline-dictionary-like-wordweb-736898/), but some of the offline suggestions were stardict and its stardict-english. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Maybe use stardict-english as a dependency and tell Lingo to parse it somehow?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "kroq-gar78", 
            "email": "kroq-gar78"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2012-03-24 01:35:38", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Again, the issue here is not quantity or availability of offline resources. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "It's simply a matter of quality.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "If someone can show that stardict or wiktionary or any other offline source offers comparable or better results than Wordnik, then it would be a suitable candidate.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
